1
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,040
-I came to ask--
-Would you

2
00:02:02,120 --> 00:02:04,080
come to the Lantern Festival
tonight with me?

3
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,680
Mr. Thatri,

4
00:02:10,759 --> 00:02:11,960
someone's here to see you.

5
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,920
An old flame showing up here?

6
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:21,360
<i>Her husband literally came with her,</i>
<i>and you're still trying to have an affair?</i>

7
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:22,960
If you're going to act like this,

8
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,720
let's just split the inheritance
once and for all.

9
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:27,680
Fine. Let's split it up and cut ties.

10
00:02:27,760 --> 00:02:29,360
Are you really moving to Bangkok

11
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,360
while the inheritance is being settled?

12
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:33,640
I'm going to rebuild my life over there.

13
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,760
Are you okay, Kajorn?

14
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:58,360
I think we should find a place
to stay the night first.

15
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:02,400
I think so too.
It's getting really late anyway.

16
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,680
I'm sure we can find
a decent hotel nearby.

17
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:12,160
A hotel?

18
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:17,400
Don't you think it'll be inappropriate?
A man and woman checking in together.

19
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:22,240
It shouldn't be a problem.
It's not like we're sharing a room.

20
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,920
Right…

21
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:45,040
I'm worried Kajorn won't buy our lie.

22
00:03:45,720 --> 00:03:47,080
He's no fool, Rajit.

23
00:03:47,160 --> 00:03:49,320
Look at how he's been
manipulating everyone.

24
00:03:49,960 --> 00:03:51,680
Trust me on this, Uncle Ree.

25
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,960
A greedy gold-digger like Kajorn

26
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:55,600
will definitely fall for it.

27
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,400
Fine.

28
00:03:58,480 --> 00:04:01,080
If you're going to lure him into a hotel

29
00:04:01,160 --> 00:04:03,200
to catch him red-handed,

30
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:06,240
there's a hotel in Phang Nga
called the Nakarin Hotel.

31
00:04:06,320 --> 00:04:08,640
It should be dark
by the time you two arrive.

32
00:04:09,920 --> 00:04:12,240
I'll bring Suda and Samornmit
to meet you there.

33
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,400
Got it.

34
00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:17,200
I'll see you at the Nakarin Hotel.

35
00:04:36,800 --> 00:04:37,760
Kajorn…

36
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:39,440
ANNOP HOTEL

37
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:41,600
I thought

38
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:45,120
we were staying
at the Nakarin Hotel tonight.

39
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:46,360
Oh.

40
00:04:46,440 --> 00:04:47,800
The Nakarin Hotel is too far.

41
00:04:47,880 --> 00:04:49,600
I figured this place is more convenient.

42
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,760
Don't worry, Rajit.

43
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:56,160
We've been together for so long,

44
00:04:56,840 --> 00:04:58,760
you should know by now
that you can trust me.

45
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,680
Of course, I trust you.

46
00:05:04,760 --> 00:05:06,440
After all, you've never crossed the line,

47
00:05:06,520 --> 00:05:09,040
besides holding my hand.

48
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:13,000
Is that bag heavy, Kajorn?

49
00:05:14,080 --> 00:05:15,200
Not at all.

50
00:05:15,280 --> 00:05:16,640
Let's go check in now, shall we?

51
00:05:17,320 --> 00:05:19,200
Kajorn.

52
00:05:19,280 --> 00:05:21,840
I really need to use the restroom.

53
00:05:21,920 --> 00:05:23,160
Of course.

54
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:33,840
Keep playing hard to get.

55
00:05:34,440 --> 00:05:36,680
You're finally mine tonight.

56
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:44,160
Do you think Ms. Samornmit
will make it in time?

57
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:46,160
Even if she doesn't,

58
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:49,200
Samornmit already knows
the location of the Nakarin Hotel.

59
00:05:50,600 --> 00:05:51,640
Right now,

60
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,000
I'm more afraid
that we'll get there too late

61
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:56,240
and Kajorn will do something to Rajit.

62
00:06:22,880 --> 00:06:24,920
Kajorn, is something the matter?

63
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,920
I'm not feeling very well.

64
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:28,720
Do you have some medicine on you?

65
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,800
Ah, yes.

66
00:06:31,880 --> 00:06:34,160
I'll bring it over to your room.

67
00:06:35,160 --> 00:06:36,000
Thank you so much.

68
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,240
Kajorn, what are you doing?

69
00:06:48,360 --> 00:06:49,720
You're finally mine.

70
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,640
What's happening to the car?

71
00:07:20,640 --> 00:07:21,800
Oh.

72
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,160
A flat tire? Right now?

73
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:27,520
Is there anything I can do to help?

74
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:30,600
It's fine. We have no choice
but to call a mechanic.

75
00:07:37,720 --> 00:07:38,640
Are you okay?

76
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,720
I'm fine.

77
00:07:51,320 --> 00:07:52,920
Stay back.

78
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:56,800
It's too late for that. You really think

79
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:59,560
-you can escape me now?
-Stop it.

80
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:17,880
So you like it rough, huh?
Where do you think you're running to?

81
00:08:32,520 --> 00:08:34,840
Could that be Ms. Samornmit?

82
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,480
Yes.

83
00:08:49,320 --> 00:08:50,480
What happened to your car?

84
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,440
A flat tire,

85
00:08:53,000 --> 00:08:54,160
but forget about that.

86
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:56,880
Right now, we have to get
to the hotel immediately.

87
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,880
I'm terrified Kajorn
will do something horrible to Rajit.

88
00:08:59,960 --> 00:09:01,600
Then get in the car.

89
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:04,440
Thank you.

90
00:09:17,040 --> 00:09:19,840
Help! Help me!

91
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,440
Help! Help me!

92
00:09:40,760 --> 00:09:42,440
What a feisty little bitch you are!

93
00:09:42,520 --> 00:09:44,200
-Ah!
-Here!

94
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,680
That's for making me bleed.

95
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:51,880
Kajorn…

96
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,000
It's finally over.

97
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,080
Playing hard to get, huh?

98
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,600
Kajorn!

99
00:10:01,680 --> 00:10:04,480
-Come here.
-Help!

100
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,640
NAKARIN HOTEL

101
00:10:09,920 --> 00:10:12,400
What room is Rajit under?
She should've checked in today.

102
00:10:12,480 --> 00:10:13,480
Just a moment, please.

103
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,240
There is no guest under the name of Rajit.

104
00:10:21,920 --> 00:10:22,960
What did you say?

105
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:25,560
There is no guest under the name of Rajit.

106
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:29,320
Mr. Thatri, didn't you arrange
to meet Rajit here at this hotel?

107
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:32,440
Rajit hasn't been hurt already, has she?

108
00:10:41,040 --> 00:10:44,120
If that bomb hadn't hit last time,

109
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,360
I would've finished you right then.

110
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:48,280
So…

111
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:51,240
the time I was drugged,

112
00:10:52,440 --> 00:10:54,160
it was your doing all along?

113
00:10:57,520 --> 00:10:58,840
If it wasn't me,

114
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:00,840
then who else?

115
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:04,440
Tonight,

116
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,040
just be a good girl.

117
00:11:09,320 --> 00:11:10,800
Stop…

118
00:11:10,880 --> 00:11:12,080
No…

119
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:26,880
You dare to fight back, huh?

120
00:11:29,440 --> 00:11:30,400
Huh?

121
00:11:30,480 --> 00:11:31,680
Ugh!

122
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:04,640
That's enough.

123
00:12:06,560 --> 00:12:08,040
Please stop, Mr. Thatri.

124
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,800
Suda…

125
00:12:19,800 --> 00:12:21,280
Kajorn!

126
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,240
Samornmit?

127
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,680
There's a hotel in Phang Nga
called the Nakarin Hotel.

128
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:36,040
It should be dark
by the time you two arrive.

129
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:39,560
I thought we were staying
at the Nakarin Hotel tonight?

130
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:40,720
Oh.

131
00:12:40,800 --> 00:12:42,240
The Nakarin Hotel is too far.

132
00:12:42,320 --> 00:12:44,040
I figured this place is more convenient.

133
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:46,600
Kajorn.

134
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:49,160
I really need to use the restroom.

135
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:50,120
Of course.

136
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,080
ANNOP HOTEL

137
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:14,160
Excuse me.

138
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:16,480
Yes, miss?

139
00:13:16,560 --> 00:13:18,040
Could you please do me a favor?

140
00:13:19,640 --> 00:13:20,880
Deliver this note

141
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:24,320
to the receptionist
at the Nakarin Hotel immediately.

142
00:13:24,400 --> 00:13:26,800
Tell them it's for a man named Thatri,

143
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:28,840
who is looking for Rajit.

144
00:13:29,440 --> 00:13:31,040
A lady gave this to me.

145
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:34,360
She said to give it to a man named Thatri,
who is looking for Rajit.

146
00:13:40,760 --> 00:13:43,000
My name is Thatri. That note is for me.

147
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,400
Here, sir.

148
00:13:47,360 --> 00:13:49,360
<i>Kajorn took me to the Annop Hotel,</i>

149
00:13:49,440 --> 00:13:51,000
<i>not the Nakarin Hotel.</i>

150
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,480
<i>Uncle Ree, please come quickly.</i>

151
00:13:54,240 --> 00:13:55,840
I know where Rajit is now.

152
00:14:05,200 --> 00:14:07,440
What on earth is going on here, Kajorn?

153
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:13,000
If you don't tell the truth,
I'll kill you with my own hands.

154
00:14:14,440 --> 00:14:16,240
Calm down, Uncle Ree.

155
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:18,120
I'm sure

156
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:20,960
Kajorn won't dare
to tell another lie after this.

157
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,120
Just tell her the truth, Kajorn.

158
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,640
You've been caught red-handed.

159
00:14:30,440 --> 00:14:32,040
Well, Kajorn?

160
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:34,840
It's exactly what it looks like.

161
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:36,640
I got you pregnant,

162
00:14:37,280 --> 00:14:39,440
and I'm drowning in gambling debts.

163
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,320
When are you going to pay?

164
00:14:45,400 --> 00:14:46,520
Are you ripping me off?

165
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:48,960
Taking your sweet time, huh?

166
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:52,360
-I'm sorry.
-When are you going to pay me back?

167
00:14:52,960 --> 00:14:54,240
I'm scared, please.

168
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,800
-Scared of dying?
-Yes. I'm so sorry.

169
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:59,200
Then you should've never borrowed from me.

170
00:15:00,240 --> 00:15:01,080
Ouch…

171
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:04,920
Phan.

172
00:15:05,560 --> 00:15:06,760
Phan, please don't shoot me.

173
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:10,080
I'll get the money
for you as fast as I can.

174
00:15:10,160 --> 00:15:12,160
Please don't kill me. I beg of you.

175
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,000
I actually believe you.

176
00:15:14,920 --> 00:15:17,840
Word on the street is that
you're marrying Yong's younger sister.

177
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:20,080
Go get their money and hand it over to me.

178
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:23,960
Or would you rather
I go talk to them myself?

179
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:27,200
Phan.

180
00:15:27,280 --> 00:15:28,640
Please don't tell Yong.

181
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,080
If he finds out,

182
00:15:30,680 --> 00:15:34,280
he'll never let Samornmit marry me.
He already hates my guts.

183
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,600
Without Samornmit,

184
00:15:36,680 --> 00:15:38,800
I'd be dead by now.

185
00:15:39,440 --> 00:15:40,280
I'm begging you.

186
00:15:43,160 --> 00:15:45,960
-Please.
-Then go get my damn money.

187
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,640
If you fail to bring it to me,

188
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:50,640
I'll go straight to Yong myself.

189
00:15:50,720 --> 00:15:51,680
Yes.

190
00:15:52,440 --> 00:15:53,480
Absolutely.

191
00:15:53,560 --> 00:15:54,960
And when that time comes,

192
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:57,480
you getting shot to pieces
won't be my business anymore.

193
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:01,280
Hey. Get him out of here.

194
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:04,200
Get up.

195
00:16:10,680 --> 00:16:14,000
Have you still not made up with Rajit yet?

196
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:18,480
I don't have the nerve
to face Rajit like this.

197
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:22,880
We are worlds apart now.

198
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:25,360
Rajit inherited a fortune

199
00:16:25,440 --> 00:16:26,920
and became filthy rich.

200
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:29,480
But look at me.

201
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,760
I'm a pauper,

202
00:16:32,760 --> 00:16:34,400
cut off from the inheritance,

203
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,640
and forced to live like this.

204
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,520
Rajit got the inheritance?

205
00:16:43,040 --> 00:16:45,160
You're friends.

206
00:16:45,240 --> 00:16:47,360
She'll surely forgive you.

207
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:52,880
Just go make up with her.

208
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:57,600
I can't stand seeing you
drowning in guilt like this forever.

209
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,280
Don't.

210
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:03,800
Everything that's happening
is just my karma.

211
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:06,680
I did such terrible things
to my own friend.

212
00:17:18,119 --> 00:17:19,920
So that's why you approached Rajit,

213
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,319
just to use her inheritance
to pay off your debts?

214
00:17:23,920 --> 00:17:26,000
Yeah, that's right.

215
00:17:30,360 --> 00:17:32,000
You must be Thatri.

216
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:34,720
My men said you asked to see me.

217
00:17:35,360 --> 00:17:36,800
Please, have a seat.

218
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:38,120
Yes.

219
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:43,440
I'm here to talk to you about Kajorn.

220
00:17:44,480 --> 00:17:47,600
About Kajorn? Is there a problem?

221
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,760
I'm sorry, but do you know
where Kajorn is right now?

222
00:17:51,840 --> 00:17:54,200
This is the very first time we've met.

223
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:56,920
Why should I share stories
about my lover with you?

224
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:59,000
If I'm not mistaken,

225
00:17:59,080 --> 00:18:02,120
Kajorn probably told you he was going home

226
00:18:02,200 --> 00:18:04,000
to gather the dowry to marry you.

227
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:05,360
Is that right?

228
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,720
And while you're pregnant,

229
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:09,920
Kajorn actually has
another dying wife elsewhere.

230
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:13,080
And now, he's scamming my niece
out of her inheritance.

231
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,920
You're trying to frame him.

232
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,920
I figured you wouldn't believe me.

233
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,640
That's why I came here,

234
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:23,000
so you could see the proof.

235
00:18:35,280 --> 00:18:37,080
Hello, Ms. Samornmit.

236
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:42,520
This is Kajorn's wife,

237
00:18:42,600 --> 00:18:44,320
the one I mentioned.

238
00:18:58,800 --> 00:19:00,640
I'm so sorry, Samornmit.

239
00:19:00,720 --> 00:19:03,280
My plan was to clear my debts,

240
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:07,320
then start fresh with you and our baby.

241
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:10,640
We can finally be a real family.

242
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:14,080
Please, forgive me.

243
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:17,400
Do you still remember

244
00:19:17,960 --> 00:19:19,600
that we're having a baby?

245
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,640
Samornmit…

246
00:19:22,200 --> 00:19:23,840
I love both you and our baby.

247
00:19:24,680 --> 00:19:26,080
Everything terrible I did,

248
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:28,920
it was only because
I wanted to be with you two.

249
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,320
That's why I did this.

250
00:19:31,360 --> 00:19:33,120
Please forgive me.

251
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:36,600
I beg you.

252
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:39,320
Please.

253
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,400
I'm so sorry.

254
00:19:49,920 --> 00:19:51,600
Thank you, everyone,

255
00:19:51,680 --> 00:19:54,040
for telling me the truth.

256
00:19:55,280 --> 00:19:57,480
No matter how furious I am,

257
00:19:57,560 --> 00:19:59,400
he is still the father of my child.

258
00:20:01,880 --> 00:20:03,360
I can't break up with him.

259
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:08,960
-But--
-If you believe this is for the best,

260
00:20:09,040 --> 00:20:10,800
we won't stop you.

261
00:20:12,720 --> 00:20:15,680
Growing up without a father
is indeed a hard life.

262
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,040
Thank you for understanding.

263
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:34,360
Since you've made your choice,
I truly wish you the best of luck.

264
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,280
Thank you.

265
00:20:37,840 --> 00:20:40,840
Well, Kajorn and I
will take our leave now.

266
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,360
Alright.

267
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,280
Let's go.

268
00:21:12,240 --> 00:21:13,320
Thank you, Samornmit,

269
00:21:13,960 --> 00:21:15,360
for being so understanding.

270
00:21:19,120 --> 00:21:20,320
Pull over.

271
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,880
Understanding?

272
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:31,520
Do you think I would ever want you
to be the father of my child?

273
00:21:32,880 --> 00:21:34,400
What are you planning to do?

274
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:37,240
Samornmit?

275
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,040
Samornmit.

276
00:21:45,040 --> 00:21:46,560
No. Samornmit.

277
00:21:46,640 --> 00:21:49,120
-Get out. Get out.
-Samornmit.

278
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,560
Out.

279
00:21:50,640 --> 00:21:52,080
No!

280
00:21:54,240 --> 00:21:56,280
Samornmit, help me.

281
00:21:56,360 --> 00:21:57,840
I'd be an idiot to help you.

282
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,880
Brother, he's all yours.

283
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:05,600
Please.

284
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:07,840
Please have mercy.

285
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:10,840
-Please.
-You bastard.

286
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,840
Please, don't!

287
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,560
Yong!

288
00:22:16,120 --> 00:22:18,120
Yong! No!

289
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:20,400
Don't do it!

290
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:31,280
Get rid of the body.

291
00:22:31,360 --> 00:22:32,680
Yes, sir.

292
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:43,480
A mother is all you need.

293
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:47,480
There's no need
for a wretched father like that.

294
00:22:49,480 --> 00:22:50,880
Drive.

295
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:08,600
Is it good?

296
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:11,400
I made it myself, you know.

297
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,520
It's delicious.

298
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,480
Your cooking is still as amazing as ever.

299
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:25,240
Of course.

300
00:23:29,240 --> 00:23:30,200
By the way,

301
00:23:30,280 --> 00:23:32,560
how are you feeling?

302
00:23:32,640 --> 00:23:35,080
I've already sent Nid to call a doctor

303
00:23:35,160 --> 00:23:37,320
to check on you.

304
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:45,440
Thank you so much, Rajit.

305
00:23:48,200 --> 00:23:52,480
I never imagined you'd still
be this kind to me after everything.

306
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:58,280
What you've been through

307
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:01,000
is far too much for me
to ever hold a grudge.

308
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,400
Let's just forget about the past.

309
00:24:09,720 --> 00:24:10,760
Rajit…

310
00:24:11,280 --> 00:24:13,720
Rajit! Are you back?

311
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:14,880
I heard from…

312
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,080
I heard from Uncle Ree.

313
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:23,480
Primprao. Suda's not feeling well.

314
00:24:23,560 --> 00:24:25,720
She's going to stay here for a while.

315
00:24:32,480 --> 00:24:35,720
How did it go?
I heard you drive Kajorn away…

316
00:24:37,440 --> 00:24:38,960
Suda.

317
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:45,920
Primprao, Nareewan.
It's good to see you again.

318
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,080
Hey, you guys.

319
00:25:03,800 --> 00:25:05,160
Don't be mad at me yet.

320
00:25:05,240 --> 00:25:07,280
Hear me out first.

321
00:25:07,360 --> 00:25:08,920
Can I just not listen?

322
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:11,200
You're always way too soft-hearted.

323
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:13,320
Exactly.

324
00:25:13,400 --> 00:25:16,840
Have you completely forgotten
what Suda did to you?

325
00:25:17,840 --> 00:25:19,240
The man I love…

326
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:23,080
and my dearest friend?

327
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,040
How could you do this?

328
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:29,720
Love doesn't leave room for three.

329
00:25:32,160 --> 00:25:34,280
Kajorn chose me,

330
00:25:35,120 --> 00:25:36,640
and I love him.

331
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:39,480
This was inevitable.

332
00:25:40,080 --> 00:25:41,040
Rajit.

333
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,720
I have something to tell you.

334
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,840
As soon as I graduate,
I'm marrying Kajorn.

335
00:25:49,520 --> 00:25:51,040
Who says I forgot?

336
00:25:51,120 --> 00:25:53,320
I remember every single thing.

337
00:25:53,400 --> 00:25:55,520
Suda has already learned her lesson.

338
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:58,680
Her life is ruined
because she fell for Kajorn.

339
00:25:58,760 --> 00:26:00,960
Honestly, I should thank her

340
00:26:01,040 --> 00:26:03,600
for helping me escape him.

341
00:26:04,200 --> 00:26:08,080
Otherwise, I'd be in her shoes right now.

342
00:26:11,960 --> 00:26:13,440
Even so,

343
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:16,520
that doesn't mean
she won't try to hurt you again.

344
00:26:17,880 --> 00:26:20,240
She's very sick right now.

345
00:26:20,320 --> 00:26:22,280
She wouldn't be capable of hurting me.

346
00:26:26,920 --> 00:26:28,080
Whatever you say.

347
00:26:28,680 --> 00:26:32,880
What Suda did to you
is simply unforgivable in my book.

348
00:26:45,080 --> 00:26:47,000
You're truly brilliant, Mr. Thatri.

349
00:26:47,080 --> 00:26:49,240
You played that lowlife like a fiddle.

350
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:52,800
It's a shame I was left out of the loop.
I wanted to see the look on his face.

351
00:26:54,280 --> 00:26:55,480
Give the credit to Rajit.

352
00:26:55,560 --> 00:26:56,920
She's the mastermind

353
00:26:57,000 --> 00:26:58,920
who put herself at risk.

354
00:27:00,800 --> 00:27:02,400
However, Kajorn is quite lucky

355
00:27:02,480 --> 00:27:04,320
to have a woman
who loves him like Samornmit,

356
00:27:04,400 --> 00:27:05,960
allowing him to get away.

357
00:27:06,040 --> 00:27:09,520
I doubt his life will be easy.

358
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,480
Marrying into a Triad family,

359
00:27:12,120 --> 00:27:14,640
if he screws up,
they'll break his bones for sure.

360
00:27:18,160 --> 00:27:21,360
Anyway, I'm sorry for not telling you
about the plan earlier.

361
00:27:21,440 --> 00:27:23,440
It caused you quite a bit of trouble.

362
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:25,760
Don't worry. I completely understand.

363
00:27:44,920 --> 00:27:46,360
You've met Primprao and Nareewan, right?

364
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:47,840
Yes.

365
00:27:48,880 --> 00:27:50,760
But they wouldn't talk to me.

366
00:27:51,400 --> 00:27:53,080
I guess they're still mad at me.

367
00:27:54,040 --> 00:27:55,320
Don't overthink it.

368
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,240
You're friends. One day,
they'll understand.

369
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,520
It's fine.

370
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,640
I deserve it.

371
00:28:03,720 --> 00:28:06,080
Nobody wants to be friends
with a traitor like me.

372
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:09,280
They'll come around once they calm down.

373
00:28:10,320 --> 00:28:11,600
Trust me.

374
00:28:14,200 --> 00:28:16,440
I truly hope so.

375
00:28:19,280 --> 00:28:22,400
Rajit mentioned she asked Nid
to call a doctor for you, right?

376
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:26,600
Yes.

377
00:28:26,680 --> 00:28:29,040
But actually, I'd rather
go somewhere else instead.

378
00:28:31,320 --> 00:28:32,640
Where is that?

379
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,920
How is your hand doing?

380
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,160
It's not a big deal. I got worse injuries
saving you from that falling horse.

381
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:25,440
Poof!

382
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:30,240
In that case, I hope
you heal quickly, Uncle Ree.

383
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:39,360
And you? How are you feeling?

384
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:41,840
I'm perfectly fine now.

385
00:29:43,280 --> 00:29:45,240
Look at you, acting so tough.

386
00:29:52,480 --> 00:29:54,400
Isn't Suda going to join us for a walk?

387
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:57,120
I know, right?

388
00:29:57,200 --> 00:29:59,840
She was the one
who asked you to bring her here.

389
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:03,160
What about Primprao and Nareewan?

390
00:30:03,240 --> 00:30:05,000
How are they?

391
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:07,840
Just thinking about it stresses me out.

392
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,240
Those two

393
00:30:10,960 --> 00:30:14,120
show no sign
of forgiving Suda anytime soon.

394
00:30:15,200 --> 00:30:17,160
They're probably just looking out for you.

395
00:30:18,160 --> 00:30:19,360
That's true.

396
00:30:19,440 --> 00:30:21,000
But I feel like

397
00:30:21,080 --> 00:30:23,440
time waits for no one,

398
00:30:24,120 --> 00:30:26,120
and it can never be reversed.

399
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:28,480
I'm afraid their stubborn pride

400
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:32,640
will leave them with regrets
for the rest of their lives.

401
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:37,920
You're right.

402
00:30:38,840 --> 00:30:40,560
If I could turn back time…

403
00:30:43,920 --> 00:30:46,040
What would you want to change, Uncle Ree?

404
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:49,880
No.

405
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:52,920
I wouldn't want to change a thing.

406
00:30:53,720 --> 00:30:55,280
Why not?

407
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:57,760
Because everything in the past

408
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,080
brought me right here today.

409
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:05,880
Are you talking about the fortune?

410
00:31:09,880 --> 00:31:10,960
Yes.

411
00:31:12,280 --> 00:31:14,120
To be right by my fortune.

412
00:31:32,600 --> 00:31:35,080
You really are a greedy man, Uncle Ree.

413
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:41,680
Let's go back to Suda.

414
00:31:42,280 --> 00:31:43,640
Let's go.

415
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,200
Suda, aren't you coming out for a walk?

416
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:56,080
You said you'd rather
see the ocean than a doctor.

417
00:31:56,680 --> 00:32:00,040
Why leave Uncle Ree
and me to walk alone like this?

418
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:04,800
Suda.

419
00:32:05,440 --> 00:32:06,600
Are you asleep?

420
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:08,360
Suda.

421
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:14,240
Suda.

422
00:32:15,160 --> 00:32:17,160
Suda. Hey.

423
00:32:17,240 --> 00:32:19,520
Suda.

424
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:20,600
Suda.

425
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:27,640
We need to get back
and call a doctor immediately.

426
00:32:28,640 --> 00:32:30,000
Yes.

427
00:32:51,160 --> 00:32:52,520
You should prepare yourself.

428
00:32:52,600 --> 00:32:54,640
She may only have a few days left.

429
00:32:57,280 --> 00:32:58,360
Yes, Doctor.

430
00:33:16,280 --> 00:33:17,400
Suda.

431
00:33:19,520 --> 00:33:20,880
You're awake?

432
00:33:23,200 --> 00:33:25,600
Why didn't you tell me
you're this seriously ill.

433
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:29,800
I've known it was too late

434
00:33:31,680 --> 00:33:35,640
ever since Mr. Thatri
took me to the hospital last time.

435
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,600
There's no cure for this.

436
00:33:48,640 --> 00:33:50,400
I'd rather spend my remaining time

437
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:52,880
seeing you guys

438
00:33:54,160 --> 00:33:56,520
one last time.

439
00:34:08,639 --> 00:34:09,800
Are you holding up okay?

440
00:34:14,080 --> 00:34:15,480
It's alright.

441
00:34:28,159 --> 00:34:30,120
You shouldn't be out of bed.

442
00:34:31,679 --> 00:34:34,040
I'm afraid your condition
will only get worse.

443
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:40,480
I just wanted to see the daylight
and feel the sun for a bit.

444
00:34:43,120 --> 00:34:44,560
Go sit over there first.

445
00:34:46,440 --> 00:34:47,800
Take it easy.

446
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:53,520
Thank you.

447
00:35:11,120 --> 00:35:12,360
Primprao.

448
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,880
Nareewan.

449
00:35:14,520 --> 00:35:16,200
I'm so glad to see you.

450
00:35:16,280 --> 00:35:17,320
Yeah.

451
00:35:17,400 --> 00:35:18,760
Glad to see you too.

452
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:22,320
How are you feeling?

453
00:35:23,040 --> 00:35:24,720
She's actually gotten a lot worse--

454
00:35:24,800 --> 00:35:26,400
I was asking Suda.

455
00:35:32,400 --> 00:35:34,440
I had no energy earlier,

456
00:35:34,520 --> 00:35:36,280
but seeing you all

457
00:35:37,240 --> 00:35:38,400
gives me strength again.

458
00:35:39,160 --> 00:35:41,360
Are you just acting dramatic, sweetie?

459
00:35:42,560 --> 00:35:43,400
Ouch.

460
00:35:43,480 --> 00:35:44,560
That hurts.

461
00:35:51,760 --> 00:35:53,200
Listen to me.

462
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:56,280
This might be the last chance

463
00:35:57,160 --> 00:35:58,840
we ever get to talk to Suda.

464
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:14,040
Good to hear you have some strength back.

465
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:16,440
Have you been able
to see your parents yet?

466
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:18,240
Not yet.

467
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,200
At this rate…

468
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:26,560
Then how about this?

469
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:28,200
The four of us

470
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:31,040
can write a letter
to your parents together.

471
00:36:31,120 --> 00:36:33,800
Nareewan can be the one to mail it out.

472
00:36:34,400 --> 00:36:37,120
Her house is right near the post office.

473
00:36:37,200 --> 00:36:38,920
Of course, I can easily drop it off.

474
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:41,160
But where are the paper and pens?

475
00:36:41,240 --> 00:36:42,960
I'll do the writing.

476
00:36:43,040 --> 00:36:44,520
I have them right here.

477
00:36:44,600 --> 00:36:45,440
Oh.

478
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,040
Come on.

479
00:36:59,280 --> 00:37:02,000
"To my dearest mother and father.

480
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:06,600
As I write this letter,

481
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,320
I cannot bring myself

482
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:12,400
to say that I am doing well.

483
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:32,600
I will love you both always.

484
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:38,120
Suda."

485
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:46,800
Here. And don't you forget
to mail it out for Suda.

486
00:37:46,880 --> 00:37:48,160
I will.

487
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,440
Hey, Suda.

488
00:37:51,520 --> 00:37:53,480
Do you feel a bit more at peace now?

489
00:37:55,080 --> 00:37:56,200
Yes.

490
00:38:15,520 --> 00:38:17,120
If there's a next life,

491
00:38:18,000 --> 00:38:20,760
I hope that I get to be friends
with you all over again.

492
00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:28,800
Don't say such things.

493
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,720
Right now, the four of us

494
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:33,160
are still friends.

495
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:35,880
And we will be friends forever.

496
00:38:48,640 --> 00:38:50,840
I'm going to the restroom.

497
00:38:51,560 --> 00:38:53,320
Do you want me to come with you?

498
00:38:54,440 --> 00:38:56,040
It's fine.

499
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:25,880
Suda.

500
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:27,840
Suda!

501
00:39:29,640 --> 00:39:30,720
Suda!

502
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,440
-Suda!
-Suda!

503
00:39:33,240 --> 00:39:34,560
-Suda!
-Suda!

504
00:39:34,640 --> 00:39:36,320
Can you hear me, Suda?

505
00:39:36,400 --> 00:39:38,920
Suda, wake up, please!

506
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:40,840
Suda, can you hear my voice?

507
00:39:41,360 --> 00:39:42,600
Suda!

508
00:39:45,720 --> 00:39:46,840
Suda!

509
00:39:48,040 --> 00:39:49,000
-Suda!
-Suda!

510
00:39:59,440 --> 00:40:05,440
PHRA NAKHON

511
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:07,840
Please forgive us

512
00:40:07,920 --> 00:40:10,520
for proceeding with the funeral

513
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:13,240
and cremation without asking you first.

514
00:40:15,320 --> 00:40:19,320
But with the war, transporting her body
back to Bangkok was too difficult.

515
00:40:21,040 --> 00:40:22,240
I understand.

516
00:40:23,480 --> 00:40:26,240
I am already so grateful

517
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:29,080
that you took care of her funeral.

518
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:32,840
Suda.

519
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:36,560
My sweet child.

520
00:40:38,440 --> 00:40:40,440
It shouldn't have ended like this.

521
00:40:42,040 --> 00:40:44,640
Why didn't you come home to your parents?

522
00:40:49,200 --> 00:40:50,240
Auntie.

523
00:40:50,840 --> 00:40:53,360
Suda was probably too ashamed to return.

524
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:55,920
Before she left,

525
00:40:56,480 --> 00:40:58,560
she had that argument with you both.

526
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,560
Once she fell ill,

527
00:41:01,640 --> 00:41:04,800
she must've felt it wasn't right
to just run back to you.

528
00:41:12,200 --> 00:41:14,280
It's all because of that vile,
worthless man!

529
00:41:14,360 --> 00:41:15,640
Where is he?!

530
00:41:15,720 --> 00:41:18,120
-I will kill him myself!
-Auntie…

531
00:41:19,600 --> 00:41:22,080
A man like that
isn't even worth your hatred, Auntie.

532
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:25,640
Though I don't know where he is
or what he's up to,

533
00:41:26,320 --> 00:41:28,040
I believe that karma is real,

534
00:41:28,680 --> 00:41:30,480
and a sinner like him will pay for it.

535
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:40,640
Auntie.

536
00:41:41,320 --> 00:41:42,800
Where is Suda's father?

537
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:47,040
He's inside.

538
00:41:47,800 --> 00:41:49,400
He's so devastated,

539
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:52,240
he couldn't bring himself to come out
and face her ashes.

540
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:21,080
Come in.

541
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,680
Are you leaving already?

542
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:30,920
Yes, Uncle.

543
00:42:32,240 --> 00:42:34,080
But before I leave,

544
00:42:35,600 --> 00:42:38,360
I have a letter from Suda for you.

545
00:42:45,000 --> 00:42:48,120
I won't read it. Take it to her mother.

546
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:52,440
But I believe Suda wanted you to read it.

547
00:42:55,120 --> 00:42:57,320
When she was writing this letter,

548
00:42:57,920 --> 00:42:59,320
she explicitly told me

549
00:43:00,160 --> 00:43:02,080
that she wanted her father to read it.

550
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:41,040
<i>To my dearest mother and father.</i>

551
00:43:41,120 --> 00:43:43,960
<i>As I write this letter,</i>

552
00:43:44,040 --> 00:43:47,040
<i>I cannot bring myself</i>
<i>to say that I am doing well.</i>

553
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:48,520
<i>But I am glad</i>

554
00:43:48,600 --> 00:43:52,080
<i>that I will no longer</i>
<i>cause you any more suffering.</i>

555
00:43:52,160 --> 00:43:55,200
<i>It was my fault for being so stubborn</i>

556
00:43:55,280 --> 00:43:57,880
<i>and disregarding your warnings.</i>

557
00:43:58,400 --> 00:44:00,240
<i>Especially yours, Father.</i>

558
00:44:01,840 --> 00:44:04,520
<i>I do not expect your forgiveness,</i>

559
00:44:04,600 --> 00:44:08,320
<i>but please do not mourn for me,</i>

560
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:11,960
<i>and do not blame yourself,</i>
<i>no matter what happens.</i>

561
00:44:12,040 --> 00:44:15,000
<i>Because I could never forgive myself</i>

562
00:44:15,080 --> 00:44:17,680
<i>if I knew I caused you that kind of pain.</i>

563
00:44:19,560 --> 00:44:22,640
<i>I will love you both always. Suda.</i>

564
00:44:45,840 --> 00:44:50,120
Uncle Ree, do you think
her parents will be okay soon?

565
00:44:50,920 --> 00:44:51,800
There's no way.

566
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:56,400
They just lost their daughter.

567
00:44:57,120 --> 00:44:59,240
They won't feel better anytime soon.

568
00:45:06,760 --> 00:45:08,520
But you did your absolute best,

569
00:45:11,280 --> 00:45:13,320
and you fulfilled Suda's final wish.

570
00:45:16,040 --> 00:45:18,400
She didn't want her parents
to blame themselves

571
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:20,360
for her unfortunate fate,

572
00:45:21,280 --> 00:45:24,160
and I'm sure they understand that now.

573
00:45:27,880 --> 00:45:29,800
Thank you for comforting me.

574
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,440
You feel better now, right?

575
00:45:38,760 --> 00:45:40,360
Go on back to the hotel alone then.

576
00:45:40,440 --> 00:45:41,760
I've got an errand to run.

577
00:45:42,960 --> 00:45:45,120
An errand? What kind of errand?

578
00:45:45,200 --> 00:45:47,080
Where are you going?

579
00:45:47,160 --> 00:45:48,440
With whom?

580
00:45:49,040 --> 00:45:50,480
Can you actually tell me,

581
00:45:50,560 --> 00:45:52,040
or is it a top-secret affair?

582
00:45:53,040 --> 00:45:55,160
You are not my parent.

583
00:45:55,240 --> 00:45:57,120
And I am not a toddler.

584
00:45:57,200 --> 00:45:58,440
Stop interrogating me.

585
00:46:00,280 --> 00:46:02,000
Fine, keep it to yourself.

586
00:46:02,080 --> 00:46:05,080
As long as you don't drag a friend
like Ms. Srichan along

587
00:46:05,160 --> 00:46:08,120
to give the people of Phuket
another massive headache again.

588
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:10,400
Rajit.

589
00:46:12,920 --> 00:46:16,080
Off you go then,
before you miss your appointment.

590
00:46:16,160 --> 00:46:18,280
I can walk back to the hotel by myself.

591
00:46:19,680 --> 00:46:20,640
I'm off then.

592
00:46:23,160 --> 00:46:24,360
If it wasn't a secret,

593
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:26,240
you should've been able to tell me.

594
00:46:43,240 --> 00:46:45,120
Take it easy, son.

595
00:46:45,200 --> 00:46:46,680
What's up, Leopard?

596
00:46:46,760 --> 00:46:49,120
So you found me here

597
00:46:49,200 --> 00:46:51,720
because you can't handle
my crazy family in Phuket, huh?

598
00:46:51,800 --> 00:46:52,880
Uh…

599
00:46:55,960 --> 00:46:57,400
You're from Phuket, Uncle?

600
00:46:58,160 --> 00:46:59,920
I am from Phuket as well.

601
00:47:01,280 --> 00:47:04,280
-Oh, no. I mean--
-This is Rajit, my niece.

602
00:47:05,400 --> 00:47:08,360
She shares Uncle Som's inheritance
with me.

603
00:47:25,880 --> 00:47:26,960
Uncle Ree.

604
00:47:27,040 --> 00:47:30,760
Why go deep with the details?

605
00:47:32,240 --> 00:47:33,520
Well…

606
00:47:34,720 --> 00:47:36,360
Oh, sweetheart,

607
00:47:36,880 --> 00:47:38,680
would you mind helping me in the kitchen?

608
00:47:38,760 --> 00:47:40,160
It's just about time for dinner.

609
00:47:43,080 --> 00:47:44,920
-Of course.
-This way, please.

610
00:47:55,760 --> 00:47:57,200
Why did you bring her here, man?

611
00:47:58,000 --> 00:47:59,760
It's a long story. I'll fill you in later.

612
00:48:17,200 --> 00:48:18,680
You look very skilled at this.

613
00:48:21,440 --> 00:48:23,120
I love cooking for myself.

614
00:48:23,200 --> 00:48:25,960
I used to do it all the time
when I was little.

615
00:48:27,560 --> 00:48:29,160
The grandchild of the wealthy Som

616
00:48:29,240 --> 00:48:31,000
actually does her own cooking?

617
00:48:33,480 --> 00:48:35,360
Do you know my grandfather, Auntie?

618
00:48:39,080 --> 00:48:41,320
Well, the Adisuan family

619
00:48:41,400 --> 00:48:44,920
is elite in Phuket.
Everyone has heard of them.

620
00:48:53,400 --> 00:48:55,240
Though I am his grandchild,

621
00:48:55,320 --> 00:48:58,160
I'm not his direct descendant.

622
00:49:00,440 --> 00:49:04,120
My grandmother was Sawai,
his younger sister.

623
00:49:04,880 --> 00:49:07,200
When she and my mother passed away,

624
00:49:07,800 --> 00:49:09,880
Grandpa took me in.

625
00:49:10,600 --> 00:49:12,240
You're lucky then.

626
00:49:13,160 --> 00:49:14,800
There are still many people

627
00:49:14,880 --> 00:49:17,240
whose relatives completely abandoned them,

628
00:49:18,880 --> 00:49:20,680
worse yet,

629
00:49:20,760 --> 00:49:23,000
cheated them out of their inheritance.

630
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:27,240
But Grandpa did feel immense guilt.

631
00:49:30,560 --> 00:49:32,880
He had two younger sisters.

632
00:49:34,480 --> 00:49:37,840
My grandmother and another.

633
00:49:39,680 --> 00:49:42,920
Yet, he hoarded
all the family fortune for himself.

634
00:49:43,920 --> 00:49:46,640
He was blinded by greed.

635
00:49:47,680 --> 00:49:50,160
He didn't share his inheritance
with his younger siblings.

636
00:49:51,960 --> 00:49:53,520
In the end,

637
00:49:53,600 --> 00:49:56,880
that greed became
a living hell in his heart.

638
00:49:58,160 --> 00:50:00,240
Until the day he died,

639
00:50:01,080 --> 00:50:03,280
he never found true happiness.

640
00:50:12,240 --> 00:50:14,240
I understand the situation now.

641
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:17,840
But you didn't have
to drag Rajit here with you.

642
00:50:17,920 --> 00:50:19,640
Our cover was almost blown.

643
00:50:20,800 --> 00:50:21,880
I had no choice.

644
00:50:21,960 --> 00:50:23,520
I'm heading back tomorrow,

645
00:50:23,600 --> 00:50:25,080
and I had to speak with you.

646
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:27,280
I didn't want to send
a letter or a telegram.

647
00:50:28,600 --> 00:50:29,560
Is it that serious?

648
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:31,200
What's going on?

649
00:50:33,960 --> 00:50:35,080
Well,

650
00:50:36,080 --> 00:50:38,120
the price of tin plummeted drastically.

651
00:50:39,560 --> 00:50:42,480
A mine owner who owed
Uncle Som money came begging for help.

652
00:50:43,480 --> 00:50:45,560
Rajit and I used the joint estate funds

653
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:46,720
to buy up his tin,

654
00:50:46,800 --> 00:50:49,920
to save him from bankruptcy
and keep his workers.

655
00:50:51,560 --> 00:50:53,480
I am truly sorry, man.

656
00:50:53,560 --> 00:50:54,800
It wasn't my money to spend,

657
00:50:54,880 --> 00:50:56,480
and I had no right to do it.

658
00:50:58,320 --> 00:51:01,000
I just couldn't watch innocent people
lose everything.

659
00:51:01,080 --> 00:51:03,160
Remembering your own past, huh?

660
00:51:06,320 --> 00:51:07,320
Forget it, man.

661
00:51:07,400 --> 00:51:10,240
You did a good deed.
Why would I get angry?

662
00:51:11,960 --> 00:51:13,160
Hey.

663
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:15,920
You're really not mad at me?

664
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:17,560
Yeah.

665
00:51:18,920 --> 00:51:20,360
What a massive relief.

666
00:51:20,440 --> 00:51:23,120
I haven't slept lately
because I was terrified you'd be angry.

667
00:51:23,200 --> 00:51:26,200
But don't worry.
All that tin is safe and sound.

668
00:51:26,280 --> 00:51:28,800
Once the war ends, you can just sell them.

669
00:51:29,880 --> 00:51:31,000
Definitely.

670
00:51:31,800 --> 00:51:34,280
It's over a thousand baht.
No way I'm letting that go.

671
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:38,000
It's not a thousand.

672
00:51:38,840 --> 00:51:40,920
Just your share alone is…

673
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:43,840
over a hundred thousand baht.

674
00:51:47,400 --> 00:51:48,400
Over a hundred thousand?

675
00:51:53,120 --> 00:51:55,880
What Grandpa Som regretted most

676
00:51:56,520 --> 00:51:58,800
was his youngest sister.

677
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:03,600
She's Uncle Ree's mother.

678
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:11,800
He wanted to see
Grandmother Suang one last time

679
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:15,560
to beg for her forgiveness,

680
00:52:16,520 --> 00:52:17,960
but he never succeeded.

681
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:22,360
She refused to forgive him

682
00:52:23,680 --> 00:52:25,320
and even rejected her share

683
00:52:25,400 --> 00:52:27,880
of the inheritance.

684
00:52:29,160 --> 00:52:30,640
That's why Grandfather

685
00:52:31,360 --> 00:52:34,160
left everything to Uncle Ree.

686
00:52:36,760 --> 00:52:38,040
If I could,

687
00:52:39,240 --> 00:52:40,920
I'd find Grandmother Suang

688
00:52:42,160 --> 00:52:44,000
and beg her

689
00:52:45,080 --> 00:52:46,960
to forgive him.

690
00:52:58,800 --> 00:53:00,440
Auntie, you're crying.

691
00:53:04,920 --> 00:53:06,200
It's nothing, dear.

692
00:53:07,400 --> 00:53:09,560
Your story just touched my heart.

693
00:53:10,600 --> 00:53:14,520
One day, I will make Uncle Ree's mother

694
00:53:14,600 --> 00:53:16,760
understand Grandpa Som's true heart.

695
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:28,720
You piece of trash!

696
00:53:28,800 --> 00:53:30,360
You're dead meat!

697
00:53:30,440 --> 00:53:32,360
-Hey!
-Come here.

698
00:53:32,440 --> 00:53:34,360
-Hey.
-You jerk.

699
00:53:34,440 --> 00:53:36,720
-Backstabber!
-Calm down.

700
00:53:36,800 --> 00:53:38,600
I already said I was sorry.

701
00:53:38,680 --> 00:53:39,720
You're wicked!

702
00:53:39,800 --> 00:53:42,280
I'm still your best friend.
Have you forgotten our bond?

703
00:53:42,360 --> 00:53:43,680
Argh!

704
00:53:43,760 --> 00:53:44,920
-Stop it.
-What is going on?

705
00:53:45,000 --> 00:53:45,920
What happened?

706
00:53:46,000 --> 00:53:47,680
What is this?

707
00:53:47,760 --> 00:53:49,200
Why are you attacking your friend?

708
00:53:49,280 --> 00:53:50,360
Whoa!

709
00:53:50,440 --> 00:53:51,720
-Mom!
-Wait, wait.

710
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:53,720
Help me. This Wild Bull
is going to kill me.

711
00:53:53,800 --> 00:53:55,120
Hold on, son.

712
00:53:55,200 --> 00:53:56,440
Why are you attacking him?

713
00:53:56,520 --> 00:53:57,600
You wicked friend.

714
00:53:57,680 --> 00:53:58,720
Mom,

715
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:00,040
do you know how much…

716
00:54:05,480 --> 00:54:06,840
How much he made me lose?

717
00:54:06,920 --> 00:54:07,960
A friend like him,

718
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:09,840
drawing blood is barely enough!

719
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:11,720
Mom, get out of the way.

720
00:54:11,800 --> 00:54:13,200
-Hey!
-Whoa!

721
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:14,360
-You're going to hit me.
-Mom!

722
00:54:14,440 --> 00:54:16,360
I'll help you.

723
00:54:16,440 --> 00:54:17,680
-Hey!
-Whoa!

724
00:54:17,760 --> 00:54:19,520
Please calm down.

725
00:54:19,600 --> 00:54:21,800
I said, you're going to hit me!

726
00:55:08,680 --> 00:55:10,080
This is absolutely delicious.

727
00:55:10,680 --> 00:55:12,880
If you hadn't helped out in the kitchen,

728
00:55:12,960 --> 00:55:15,000
I'd never get to eat something this good.

729
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:18,320
It's not that big of a deal.

730
00:55:18,400 --> 00:55:20,400
It's all thanks to your guidance.

731
00:55:20,480 --> 00:55:22,960
I'm really not that skilled.

732
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:36,080
Here, have some Moo Hong. Eat up.

733
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:37,920
You can't find this often during wartime.

734
00:55:40,720 --> 00:55:42,280
You think buttering me up is the way?

735
00:55:42,960 --> 00:55:44,160
I haven't forgotten.

736
00:55:54,120 --> 00:55:55,120
By the way,

737
00:55:55,200 --> 00:55:59,040
how much money did he make you lose?
Why do you seem so furious?

738
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:02,320
It's not lost. It just changed form.

739
00:56:03,240 --> 00:56:04,240
We'll get it back soon.

740
00:56:14,720 --> 00:56:15,920
Don't pay them any mind.

741
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:18,160
Friends bicker like this all the time.

742
00:56:18,240 --> 00:56:20,960
Have some of this Kaeng Som instead.

743
00:56:22,520 --> 00:56:23,880
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

744
00:56:38,080 --> 00:56:38,960
Tri.

745
00:56:40,240 --> 00:56:41,280
Sasi.

746
00:56:41,360 --> 00:56:43,360
Is she just another friend,
like Ms. Srichan?

747
00:56:43,440 --> 00:56:44,680
She's my ex-fiancée.

748
00:56:45,400 --> 00:56:47,640
I'd like to talk about Ms. Sasitorn.

749
00:56:47,720 --> 00:56:50,040
Looking for intel on your rival?

750
00:56:51,360 --> 00:56:53,040
You must be jealous.

751
00:56:53,120 --> 00:56:54,120
But they're husband and wife.

752
00:56:54,200 --> 00:56:55,800
It doesn't matter.

753
00:56:55,880 --> 00:56:57,760
Once we're back in Bangkok,

754
00:56:57,840 --> 00:56:59,400
I'll give you a divorce.

755
00:57:01,760 --> 00:57:03,120
<i>Are you secretly seeing Tri?</i>

756
00:57:03,200 --> 00:57:05,640
<i>We're uncle and niece.</i>

757
00:57:06,320 --> 00:57:07,800
Who would think that way?

758
00:57:07,880 --> 00:57:09,200
What if he weren't your uncle?

759
00:57:09,840 --> 00:57:11,240
Would you?

760
00:57:41,480 --> 00:57:43,200
Subtitle translation by:
Khathathong Thongtumlueng
